.Dd March 27, 2026
.Dt CHMOD 1
.Os Kayako
.Sh NAME
.Nm chmod
.Nd change file mode bits
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl R
.Ar mode
.Ar file ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility modifies the file mode bits of the
.Ar file
operands.
.Pp
The
.Ar mode
can be an octal number or a symbolic mode string.
A symbolic mode string is a comma-separated list of operations in the format:
.Pp
.Bk -words
.Op Ar who
.Ar op
.Op Ar perm
.Ek
.Pp
The
.Ar who
symbols
.Sy u , g , o ,
and
.Sy a
specify user, group, other, and all permissions respectively.
The
.Ar op
symbols
.Sy + , - ,
and
.Sy =
specify adding, removing, or absolute setting of permissions.
The
.Ar perm
symbols
.Sy r , w ,
and
.Sy x
specify read, write, and execute permissions.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl R
Recursive. Change the mode of the
.Ar file
hierarchies rooted in the specified operands.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Grant execute permission to everyone:
.Pp
.Dl $ chmod a+x binary
.Pp
Set exact permissions using octal:
.Pp
.Dl $ chmod 644 index.html
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr chmod 2 ,
.Xr chown 8 ,
.Xr ls 1
